\v 2 Tola's sons¦190658 were Uzzi¦190660, Refayah, Yeriel¦190662, Yahmai¦190663, Ibsam¦190664, and Shemuel¦190665 \add who all became\add* leaders of their clans. \add ≈There were strong warriors in the record of Tola's descendants in each generation¦190673\add*. (During the time that David¦190676 was Yisrael's king, there were 22,600 such men.)
\p
\v 3 Uzzi's¦190686 son was Yizrahyah. Yizrahyah's five sons were Mikael, Ovadyah, Yoel¦190692, and Yishiyah. They were all \add ≈leaders of their¦190696 clans\add*.
\v 4 Along with them according to their \add ≈family records\add*, were 36,000 troops¦190702 in the army, because they¦190710 \add ≈had numerous\add* wives¦190711 and sons¦190712.
