\p
\v 14 Manashsheh¦190835 had sons¦190834 by his \add ≈Syrian¦190840\add* (Heb. Aramean¦190840) slave wife. She gave birth to Asriel¦190836, and Makir¦190844 (\add who became\add* the father¦190845 of Gilead¦190846).
\v 15 Makir \add ≈married\add* a wife from the Huppites and Shuppites. (His sister's¦190854 name was Maakah.) \add ≈Another\add* descendant was Tselofehad and he had daughters¦190861.
\v 16 Makir's¦190867 wife¦190865 (\add also called¦190869\add* Maakah) bore a son and named him Peresh¦190871 (and named his brother Sheresh¦190874) and his sons¦190875 were Ulam¦190876 and Rakem.
