\p
\v 40 All those were Asher's¦191142 descendants¦191140, \add ≈clan leaders\add*, chosen¦191147, very strong, \add ≈leaders of leaders\add*. And listed in their genealogy¦191152 in the army for war, their number¦191155, 26,000 men.
\c 8
\s1 Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Benjamin; The Genealogy of Saul the Benjamite; The Descendants of Benjamin
\p
\v 1 Benyamin¦191162 had sons: Bela¦191166, Ashbel¦191168, Aharah¦191170,
\v 2 Nohah, and¦191175 the fifth¦191176, Rafa¦191175.
\p
\v 3 Bela's¦191181 sons¦191180 were Addar¦191182, Gera¦191183, Abihud¦191184,
\v 4 Avishua, Naaman¦191187, Ahoah¦191188,
\v 5 Gera, Shefufan, and Huram¦191192.
\p
\v 6 \add One of Gera's sons¦191195 was\add* Ehud¦191196. \add ≈His descendants were leaders of their clans who lived\add* in Geba¦191202 \add city\add*, but were taken into exile to Manahat¦191206.
\v 7 Ehud's sons were Naaman, Ahijah¦191209, and Gera. Gera \add ≈was the one who led them\add* \add when they moved to Manahat\add*. He \add ≈was the father¦191213 of\add* Uzza and Ahihud¦191219.
\p
\v 8 \add Another descendant of Benyamin was\add* Shaharayim¦191221 \add ≈who lived\add* in the Moab¦191224 countryside¦191223. He \add ≈divorced\add* his wives¦191233 Hushim¦191229 and¦191230 Baara¦191232
\v 9 and fathered¦191235 \add sons\add* with his wife Hodesh¦191238: Yobab¦191242, Tsivya¦191245, Mesha¦191248, Malkam¦191251,
\v 10 Yeuts, Sakeya, and Mirmah¦191261. They all became leaders of their clans.
\v 11 (He had fathered¦191268 Avituv and¦191272 Elpaal¦191274 by Hushim.)
