\v 16 Ovadyah (Shemayah's¦191794 son, Shemayah was Galal's¦191797 son, Galal was Yedutun's son), and Berekyah who lived in one of the villages¦191809 where the Netofat people lived (Berekyah was Asa's¦191804 son, Asa was Elkanah's¦191807 son).
\p
\v 17 From Levi's descendants who returned to Yehudah who guarded the temple gates there was Shallum, Akkuv, Talmon¦191815, Ahiman¦191816, and some of their relatives¦191817. Shallum was their leader.
\v 18 Those descendents¦191830 of Levi¦191831 were gatekeepers¦191828 at the King's Gate on the east \add ≈even at the present time\add*.
\p
\v 19 Shallum was Kore's¦191836 son, Kore was Evyasaph's son, and Evyasaph was Korah's son. Shallum and his relatives¦191843 from his clan (Korah's descendants), had the duty of being gatekeepers, responsible to guard the entrances¦191860 to Yahweh's temple as their¦191854 ancestors¦191854 had done.
\v 20 \add ≈Previously\add* Pinehas (Eleazar's¦191865 son) \add ≈had supervised\add* the gatekeepers. Yahweh¦191870 was with \add @Pinehas\add*.
\p
\v 21 Zekaryah (Meshelemyah's¦191876 son) was gatekeeper¦191877 of the entrance¦191878 to the assembly tent.
\v 22 \add ≈Altogether, there were 212 men chosen¦191883 to guard the gates\add*. \add ≈The records of the clans in their villages¦191890 listed their names\add*. \add King\add* David¦191894 and \add ≈the prophet\add* Shemuel \add (Samuel¦191895)\add* \add ≈appointed¦191893 them because they¦191889 were dependable\add*.
\v 23 They and their¦191900 sons \add watched\add* over the gates¦191903 of Yahweh's house, i.e., the \add ≈sacred\add* tent, as guards¦191910.
\v 24 There were gatekeepers¦191915 on each of the \add temple's\add* four¦191912 sides¦191913: east, west, north¦191918, and¦191919 south¦191919.
\v 25 Their relatives¦191921 in their villages¦191922 would come in from time to time \add to relieve them\add* for seven¦191924 days¦191925
\v 26 because the four¦191937 leaders of the gatekeepers¦191939 were Levites¦191941, and they were \add also\add* \add ≈trusted¦191935 to supervise\add* the chambers¦191945 and the treasuries¦191947 in God's¦191949 residence.
\v 27 They¦191954 would \add ≈spend the night¦191955\add* around¦191951 the \add ≈temple\add* while they were in charge, and \add ≈would open it with the key each\add* morning.
\rem /s1 The Other Levites
\p
\v 28 Some of them \add ≈monitored the utensils used in the activities\add*—counting them as they brought¦191975 them out and¦191976 \add ≈when they put them away\add* \add again\add*.
\v 29 \add ≈Others\add* took care of the containers and utensils used in the sanctuary¦191988, along with the fine flour¦191991, the wine and oil, and the frankincense and spices¦191995.
\v 30 Some of the priests¦192000 mixed¦192001 \add the fragrances and\add* spices¦192003.
\p
\v 31 There was a Levite¦192008 \add named\add* Mattithiah¦192005 (the oldest son of Shallum¦192011, who was a descendant of Korah) whose official duty \add ≈was supervising the baking of the flat breads\add*.
\v 32 Some of Kohat's descendants prepared¦192029 the rows of bread¦192027 to \add laid out on the sacred table\add* every rest day.
\p
\v 33 Some of Levi's descendants were \add temple musicians and\add* singers¦192035. The leaders of those families stayed in the temple accommodations. They \add ≈didn't have other duties\add* because they they \add were expected to\add* serve day¦192044 and night¦192045.
\v 34 Those were the heads¦192050 of the Levite¦192052 \add ≈families¦192051\add* according¦192053 to their¦192053 generations¦192053 \add and\add* they¦192056 lived in Yerushalem¦192057.
\s1 King Shaul's ancestors and descendants
